        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>The requested sensitivity is justified by the need to detect the HCN(4-3) line with a S/N&gt;6.
The remaining targeted observations of the H26alpha line and continuum have S/N ratios greater than 6.

The requested angular resolution of 0.13'' (~2 pc) is based on the scale of the structures we are targeting. A Sgr B2 like giant molecular cloud has a size of ~120 pc, while its components (e.g., Sgr B2 main) have sizes of ~0.1 pc.

The mosaic pattern is chosen so that we can recover the emission from HCN over the whole starburst region of NGC253.
The HCN emission is concentrated over the central starburst with a major axis ~20'' and a position angle of 64Â° (counterclockwise).
This ragion can be maped with the proposed 5 pointing mosaic with the 12-m array. This only requires one pointing from ACA and the TP array.
</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
